100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 27, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on international disarmament and the ongoing tensions in the Far East. In the United States, the trial of the Scopes "Monkey" Case continued to capture national attention, as the debate over teaching evolution in schools intensified. Meanwhile, political unrest in Germany grew as the Nazi Party gained traction against the backdrop of economic strife.
